<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - POWER DISTRIBUTION AND GROUNDS -
        Noise Kill
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Noise Kill</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Fault Detection Management</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The testing method for troubleshooting the electrical systems portrayed in this manual is a
                        basic voltage test. An alternative method of checking for voltage drops within a given circuit
                        may be a quicker method of identifying an exact problem.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>A malfunction in the noise kill system will be apparent when systems remain active when the noise kill
                is activated.
            </para>
            <para>Problems with noise kill system may be due to loose power connections, loose ground connections, a
                blown fuse, a faulty relay, open circuits or circuits shorted to ground.
            </para>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f08290207">Noise Kill Diagram</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f08290207" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g08290207.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="484px"/>
                <caption>Noise Kill Circuit Diagram - Always Refer to Circuit Diagram Book for Latest Circuit
                    Information
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>(1006) BODY BUILDER CONNECTOR
                        <callout2>LOCATED AT LEFT SIDE VEHICLE AT FLASHER PLATE</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>(1011) FUSE BLOCK
                        <callout2>LOCATED LEFT SIDE VEHICLE AT FLASHER PLATE</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <table id="t08290007" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <title>Noise Kill Voltage Checks</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.16in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="3.30in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="4" spanname="S1T6"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T6">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="BOLD">Ignition/Accessory Feed Relay Voltage Check</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Check with key switch in on position and ignition/accessory feed relay removed.
                                </para>
                                <para>
                                    <hotlnk document="s08290_X08290001.xml" xrefid="x08290001">Bench test relay</hotlnk>
                                    . If relay fails bench test, replace relay and check for faults.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>Test Points</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                <para>Spec.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>Ignition/accessory feed relay cavity 86 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>If voltage is missing, check for blown fuse F11 and check for open or short in
                                    circuits 16 WHT 63 and A89HH.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Ignition/accessory feed relay cavity 86 to 85.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If voltage is missing, check for open or short to high in circuit 16 WHT 40.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Ignition/accessory feed relay cavity 30 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If voltage is missing, check for blown fuse #20 and check for open or short in
                                    circuit 16 BLK 63.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="BOLD">Noise Kill Switch Voltage Checks</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Check with key in on position and ignition/accessory feed relay installed.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Points</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Spec.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connector C34 cavity 2 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If voltage is missing, check for open or short in circuit 16 BLK 40.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connector C34 cavity 2 to 3.</para>
                                <note>
                                    <para>Noise kill circuits should deactivate during this test.</para>
                                </note>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If voltage is missing, check for open or short to high in circuit 16 BLU 69.
                                </para>
                                <para>If noise kill circuits deactivate during this test, replace noise kill switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="BOLD">Noise Kill Solenoid Voltage Checks</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Check with key in on position, noise kill switch closed and ignition/accessory
                                    feed relay installed.
                                </para>
                                <para>
                                    <hotlnk document="s08290_X08290001.xml" xrefid="x08290001">Bench test relay</hotlnk>
                                    . If relay fails bench test, replace relay and check for faults.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Points</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Spec.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Noise kill solenoid cavity 86 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If voltage is missing, check for open or short in circuits 16 BLU 69, 16 BLK 40
                                    and 16 BLK 63.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Noise kill solenoid cavity 86 to 85.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If voltage is missing, check for open or short to high in circuit 16 WHT 69.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
